OL,3,CLGBTQ+ asylum seekers in the UK: The
OL,4,Cstruggles of fleeing violence
OL,6,FSpeaking of the dream she had when
OL,7,Fcoming to the UK, Virginia said: "I
OL,8,Fwas hoping I'll get a good welcome
OL,9,Fhere. They will accept me and they'll
OL,10,Fgive me safety and I will be able to
OL,11,Flive a normal life. But it has been
OL,12,Fvery difficult."
OL,14,FVirginia's been stuck in limbo ever
OL,15,Fsince she arrived, living in a home
OL,16,Ffunded by a charity in Birmingham. Her
OL,17,Fstatus as a failed asylum seeker means
OL,18,Fshe can't open a bank account, she
OL,19,Fcan't get a job, and she relies on
OL,20,Fhandouts for clothes and regularly
OL,21,Fuses a food bank.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/17
