OL,6,F"But I remember the interpreter
OL,7,Fbecause he was a man. And when I was
OL,8,Ftalking about my partner, it (the
OL,9,Finterpretations) was different. In my
OL,10,Flanguage what you call a partner is
OL,11,Fdifferent from a friend, but his
OL,12,Finterpretation was the same
OL,13,Fthing...and when I read my interview,
OL,14,Fso many things got mixed in the
OL,15,Finterpretation as I believe because he
OL,16,Fwas an elderly man, he was not much
OL,17,Faware about issues about homosexuality
OL,18,For people who are gay."
OL,20,FVirginia's a part of a group called
OL,21,FStories of Hope and Home.
