OL,6,FHer rejection means she now has to
OL,7,Fattend her local immigration reporting
OL,8,Fcentre in Solihull once a month.
OL,10,FThere she could be indefinitely
OL,11,Fdetained. She goes in not knowing if
OL,12,Fshe'll come back out.
OL,14,FVirginia's fears about being deported
OL,15,Fare highlighted in these statistics
OL,16,Ffrom the Home Office, which show that
OL,17,Fwhile the number of forced returns
OL,18,Fsteadily fell for twenty years, since
OL,19,F2021, they've been on the up - and are
OL,20,Fnow at a four-year high.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G14/17
